+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:83
+#, php-format
+msgid "PHP requires that you set a timezone in your php.ini before using date functions, or it will emit a warning. If this isn't possible (for instance, because you are using HPHP) you can set some valid constant for %s here and Phabricator will set it on your behalf, silencing the warning."
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:97
+msgid "Set a string Phabricator should use to prefix cookie names."
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:103
+#, php-format
+msgid "Prefix cookie with \"%s\""
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:160
+#, php-format
+msgid "These paths get appended to your %s environment variable."
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:164
+#, php-format
+msgid ""
+"Phabricator occasionally shells out to other binaries on the server. An example of this is the `%s` command, used to syntax-highlight code written in languages other than PHP. By default, it is assumed that these binaries are in the %s of the user running Phabricator (normally 'apache', 'httpd', or 'nobody'). Here you can add extra directories to the %s environment variable, for when these binaries are in non-standard locations.\n"
+"\n"
+"Note that you can also put binaries in `%s` (for example, by symlinking them).\n"
+"\n"
+"The current value of PATH after configuration is applied is:\n"
+"\n"
+"  lang=text\n"
+"  %s"
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:211
+msgid "Array containing list of uninstalled applications."
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:235
+msgid "Run Silently"
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:236
+msgid "Run Normally"
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:238
+msgid "Stop Phabricator from sending any email, etc."
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:241
+msgid ""
+"This option allows you to stop Phabricator from sending any data to external services. Among other things, it will disable email, SMS, repository mirroring, and HTTP hooks.\n"
+"\n"
+"This option is intended to allow a Phabricator instance to be exported, copied, imported, and run in a test environment without impacting users. For example, if you are migrating to new hardware, you could perform a test migration first, make sure things work, and then do a production cutover later with higher confidence and less disruption. Without this flag, users would receive duplicate email during the time the test instance and old production instance were both in operation."
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:271
+#, php-format
+msgid "Config option '%s' is invalid. The URI must start with %s' or '%s'."
+msgstr ""
+
+#: applications/config/option/PhabricatorCoreConfigOptions.php:282
